        "messages": {
          "values": [
            {
              "content": "=You are a system that prepares documents for semantic search (RAG).\n\nYour task is to transform the input text into structured, high-quality chunks with metadata.\n\nOUTPUT FORMAT (STRICT):\nReturn a JSON array of objects. Each object must have:\n\n{\n\"text\": \"string\",\n\"source\": \"string\",\n\"chunk_index\": number,\n\"chunk_id\": string\n}\n\ncontent: the cleaned and structured chunk text\nsource: a short identifier of the document (infer from context if not provided, otherwise use \"unknown\")\nchunk_index: incremental index starting from 0\nchunk_id: must be exactly source + \"_\" + chunk_index\n\nRULES:\n\nEach chunk must contain COMPLETE information.\nMinimum 3 sentences per chunk.\nMaximum ~150 words.\nDO NOT create small or meaningless chunks.\nAvoid titles alone.\nAvoid slogans, headers, or isolated phrases.\nNEVER create a chunk that is only a title, heading, label, or course name.\nIf the text does not contain explanatory or actionable information, DISCARD it.\nGroup related content into the same chunk.\nMerge paragraphs that belong to the same topic.\nRemove noise:\nIgnore branding, slogans, repeated headers, or irrelevant text.\nPreserve meaning:\nDo not lose important information.\nKeep explanations complete.\nPrefer fewer high-quality chunks over many small ones.\nDo NOT split sentences.\nEach chunk must start and end at natural sentence boundaries.\nIgnore:\nlegal disclaimers\ninstitutional policies\ngeneric company descriptions\nOnly include information that helps answer real user questions.\nUseful information includes:\nskills learned\ntechnologies used\nhow something works\nsteps, processes, or explanations\noutcomes, results, or capabilities\nExclude vague or generic content such as:\n\"this course is constantly updated\"\n\"high quality experience\"\n\"designed for the modern world\"\nany generic marketing language\nEach chunk must be information-dense.\nAvoid chunks that are too general, repetitive, or low in informational value.\nPrioritize technical, educational, or explanatory content over descriptive or promotional text.\nIf a chunk contains multiple distinct topics, split them into separate chunks.\nAvoid duplicate chunks:\nIf multiple parts of the text repeat the same idea or phrase, include it only once.\nDo NOT generate semantically redundant chunks.\nEach chunk must provide UNIQUE value.\nIf removing the chunk does not reduce the overall understanding, DISCARD it.\nDiscard low-value text:\nStandalone titles\nSection names\nNavigation elements\nRepeated course names\nAny content shorter than 2 full sentences\nMetadata rules:\nchunk_index must increment sequentially (0, 1, 2, ...)\nsource must be consistent across all chunks from the same input\nIf a clear title, filename, or context exists, use it as source\nIf not, use \"unknown\"\nchunk_id must follow: source + \"_\" + chunk_index\nQuality over quantity:\nIt is better to return fewer chunks than to include low-quality ones.\nLanguage requirement (MANDATORY):\nALL chunks MUST be written in Spanish.\nIf the input text is in another language, TRANSLATE it to Spanish before chunking.\nDo NOT mix languages inside a chunk.\nEnsure the Spanish is natural, clear, and technically accurate.\nDO NOT include explanations outside the JSON.\n\nIMPORTANT:\n\nReturn ONLY valid JSON\nEscape all quotes inside strings using \"\nDo not include markdown (no ```json)\n\nReturn ONLY the JSON array.\n\nTEXT: {{ $json.markdown || $json.content }}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "builtInTools": {},
        "options": {}
